comments:
Abolished 30.9.1897 to become the separate parishes of Appleby 
    Magna North and Appleby Magna South (both in Leicestershre).

Created 30.9.1898 from the parishes of Appleby Magna North and 
    Appleby Magna South. See also Table 2, note (g).

Created 30.9.1897 from the Derbyshire part of the parish of Appleby. 
    Abolished 30.9.1898 and added to the parish of Appleby Magna.

Created 30.9.1897 from the Leicestershire part of the parish of 
    Appleby. Abolished 30.9.1898 and added to the parish of Appleby Magna.
See Table 2, note (g).

Created 1894 out of the part of the parish of Ashby de la Zouch 
    in Ashby Woulds Urban District. See also Table 2, note (g).
See Table 2, notes (a), (g) and (i).

That part which until 1.4.1936 formed part of the parish of 
    Thringstone. See aso Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Ashby de 
    la Zouch and Ashby Woulds.

That part which until 1.4.1938 formed part of the parish of 
    Hartshorn. See also Table 2, note (f).
See Table 2, note (f).

That part which until 1.4.1936 formed part of the parish of 
    Whitwick. See aso Table 2, note (h).

Transferred from Derbyshire to Leicestershire on 30.9.1897. See 
    also Table 2, notes (e) and (g).

Created 29.9.1894 out of the parishes of Ravenstone & Snibston, 
    Whitwick, Hugglescote & Donnington and Swannington. See also Table 2, note 
    (g).
See Table 2, note (g).
See Table 2, note (f).
See Table 2, notes (g) and (i).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Coalville 
    and Ibstock. See also Table 2, note (i).

That part which until 1.4.1936 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Heather and Hugglestone & Donington. See aso Table 2, note (i).

That part which until 1.4.1936 formed part of the parish of 
    Marfield. See aso Table 2, note (i).

Transferred from Derbyshire to Leicestershire on 30.9.1897. See 
    also Table 2, notes (d) and (g).

Created 29.9.1894 out of the parish of Nether & Over Seal. Transferred 
    from Leicestershire to Derbyshire on 1.4.1897. See also Table 2, note (f).
See Table 2, note (g).

On 30.9.1897 the part in Derbyshire was transferred to Leicestershire, so that thereafter 
    Oakthorpe & Donisthorpe was entirely in Leicestershire. See also Table 2, note (g).
See Table 2, note (g).
Abolished 29.9.1894 to become the separate parishes of Overseal and Netherseal.

Created 29.9.1894 out of the parish of Nether & Over Seal. Transferred 
    from Leicestershire to Derbyshire on 1.4.1897. See also Table 2, note (f).

The part in Derbyshire was transferred to Leicestershire on 
    25.3.1884. See also Table 2, note (g).

Abolished 25.3.1884 and added to the parish of Ravenstone 
    with Snibstone.

Created 25.3.1884 out of the parishes of Ravenstone, 
    Packington and Ashby de la Zouch. See also Table 2, note (g).
See Table 2, notes (b) and (f).
See Table 2, note (g).

That part which until 1.4.1938 formed part of the parish of 
    Hartshorn. See also Table 2, note (f).
See Table 2, note (g).

Transferred from Derbyshire to Leicestershire on 30.9.1897. See 
    also Table 2, note (g).

That part which until 1.4.1938 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Hartshorn and Woodville. See also Table 2, note (f).
See Table 2, note (g).
See Table 2, note (g).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Smisby.

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Coalville, 
    Coleorton, Swannington, Osgathorpe, Belton and Worthington. See also Table 
    2, note (h).
See Table 2, notes (b), (c) and (f).

Abolished 1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Coalville 
    and Charley. See also Table 2, note (h).

Transferred from Derbyshire to Leicestershire on 30.9.1897. Abolished 
    1.4.1936 and divided between the parishes of Ashby de la Zouch, Oakthorpe & Donisthorpe and Measham.
Created 30.9.1897 out of the parishes of Ashby Woulds, Hartshorn and Blackfordby. See also Table 2, note (f).
See Table 2, note (g).
